value.title: Trump has more in common with Lincoln than you might think
value.excerpt: Lincoln governed during the most divided era in our nation’s history — Trump is governing in the most acrimonious period since.

value.title: 'This was avoidable': Trump has been downplaying the virus from the start
value.excerpt: In recent weeks, Trump has put himself and others at risk by holding mass gatherings, some indoors, and shunning mask use while claiming the end of the virus was just around the corner.

value.title: Pelosi: Trump diagnosis 'tragic,' hopefully leads to 'saner approach' to pandemic
value.excerpt: Speaker Nancy Pelosi said that President Trump’s COVID-19 diagnosis is “tragic” and “very sad,” but predictable, given his frequent contact with crowds.

value.title: Joe Biden says he and Jill Biden tested negative for coronavirus
value.excerpt: Joe Biden confirmed Friday that he and his wife, Jill, tested negative for the coronavirus, days after the former vice president appeared on the debate stage with President Trump, and hours after Trump revealed he and first lady Melania Trump tested positive.

value.title: Melania Trump announces she has 'mild symptoms' of coronavirus
value.excerpt: First lady Melania Trump said Friday that she is experiencing "mild symptoms" but is "looking forward to a speedy recovery" following her Covid-19 diagnosis.

value.title: No one wore a mask during Trump debate prep, Chris Christie says
value.excerpt: Former N.J. Gov. Chris Christie revealed that no one in the room was wearing a mask when a small group of people gathered in the White House's map room on Monday to help prep President Trump for the first debate.

value.title: Ex-White House physician: Trump is ‘asymptomatic,’ will be ready for next debate
value.excerpt: President Trump will "absolutely" be ready before the next presidential debate against Joe Biden, his former White House physician tells "Fox & Friends."

value.title: Donald Trump quarantines after positive Covid test; Mike Pence tests negative – live updates

value.title: Vice President Mike Pence and Karen Pence test negative for coronavirus, spokesman says
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence and second lady Karen Pence tested negative for Covid-19 Friday morning, according to a statement tweeted by spokesperson Devin O'Malley.

value.title: Boris Johnson wishes Trump 'speedy recovery' from COVID-19
value.excerpt: UK Prime Minister Boris Johnson wished President Trump a "speedy recovery" Friday, hours after he and First Lady Melania Trump tested positive for COVID-19.

value.title: ‘If He Doesn’t Win Ohio, It’s Over’: Trump Slips in the Heartland
value.excerpt: Four years ago, the president easily won Ohio by building a balanced coalition among white voters across educational lines. But his support has waned since then, particularly in the suburbs.

value.title: Trump's positive Covid-19 test throws country into fresh upheaval
value.excerpt: A country already unnerved by a devastating health catastrophe and a turbulent political season faced fresh upheaval Friday as Americans awoke to news President Donald Trump had contracted coronavirus.

value.excerpt: Former NFL star Herschel Walker turned to Twitter Thursday to take issue with a Trump-Biden debate moment regarding far-left and far-right groups and the roles they play in unrest that has rocked cities across the country.

value.title: Comey 'blatantly accused' Trump of 'horrible things' without evidence: Sen. Mike Lee
